Description: Fragment of pottery transport amphora. Oval handle at neck join, downcurving. Rectangular stamp. Clay medium purplish brown; mixed inclusions, little mica.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.31, 36). There are at least seven examples in the Benaki collection, Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0039)
